  <brief_title>Subclinical Hypothyroidism and Acute Anterior Myocardial Infarction: Is it Cardio-protective or Not?</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Hillel Yaffe Medical Center</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Hillel Yaffe Medical Center</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study plans to investigate whether recovery of the heart function after acute anterior
      myocardial infarction is dependent upon improvement in thyroid gland functioning.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <overall_status>Not yet recruiting</overall_status>
  <start_date>January 2017</start_date>
  <completion_date type="Anticipated">April 2017</completion_date>
  <primary_completion_date type="Anticipated">April 2017</primary_completion_date>
  <study_type>Observational</study_type>
  <has_expanded_access>No</has_expanded_access>
